# UI preview assets for pull requests

When you change UI files (`client/src/**`, `client/index.html`, `client/public/**`), every commit must include refreshed assets under `.github/ui-preview/`. Pre-commit blocks commits that skip this.

## Screenshot vs video

| Change type | Command | Output |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Any UI change (default) | `cd client && npm run ui:preview` | both files + validation |
| Layout / copy only | `cd client && npm run ui:screenshot` | `app-shell.png` (also refresh video if behavior changed) |
| Slideshow / navigation / timers | `cd client && npm run ui:preview` | must show slide change in `app-flow.webm` |

**Do not** commit `ui:video` alone after slideshow/timer changes — it produces a ~15KB useless clip. `ui:preview` runs capture then `validate.mjs` (min size/duration).

Run capture **before** committing UI work. Stage `.github/ui-preview/` with the UI files in the same commit.

## Opening / updating a PR

1. Ensure latest commits that touch UI also updated preview assets.
2. In the PR description, embed the assets so reviewers see them immediately:

```markdown
## UI preview
![App shell](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OWNER/REPO/BRANCH/.github/ui-preview/app-shell.png)
https://github.com/OWNER/REPO/blob/BRANCH/.github/ui-preview/app-flow.webm
```

Use **`raw.githubusercontent.com`** for the screenshot — relative `.github/...` paths do not render in GitHub PR descriptions.

3. Do not open a PR with UI-only changes and no updated preview files — CI will fail.

First-time setup on a machine: `npx playwright install chromium` from `client/`.
